<paragraph id="4846DC9BACF1287AB02486CEE6E8A6BC" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="E7431F4558BA57DDB36C705987B263F6" LSID="49782ADB-BA9B-469E-D7A6-B74E3626948B" authority="Puthz, 1981" authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus persicus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">Stenus persicus Puthz, 1981</taxonomicName>
<figureCitation id="F7E0D80AC4D86913D32EF22D2495F698" captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 12. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 7. Stenus circularis species group: ○ Stenus planifrons robustus; 8. Stenus clavicornis species group: ○ Stenus caspius, ● Stenus providus providus; 9. Stenus comma species group: ■ Stenus aereus, ○ Stenus asiaticus, ● Stenus bicornis, ▲ Stenus biguttatus, □ Stenus comma comma; 10. Stenus cordatus species group: ○ Stenus araxis, ● Stenus turk; 11. Stenus crassus and Stenus fornicatus species groups: ■ Stenus crassus, △ Stenus formicetorum, ○ Stenus fornicatus; 12. Stenus glacialis species group: ➕ Stenus armeniacus, ▲ Stenus hospes, ■ Stenus limicola, ○ Stenus medus, ▲ Stenus parcior, □ Stenus persicus, ● Stenus schah." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures7-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74429" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
, Suppl. material 1
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="78D1397A8B997F2D9D7BE41C10149878" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" type="chorology">
<paragraph id="C5DA4544E4229E01607D54B13CE61142" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Chorology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="904FDA8721302837CD11D0763B939F85" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="0333C9054280DDE1DD8A7F91E319CD45" authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus persicus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis id="FA9B8A295884F34E135A082D24259CF1" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Stenus persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be endemic to Azerbaijan and western Iran (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6809C25CAE750A9B3FBF0C2C2FD8F350" captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 12. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 7. Stenus circularis species group: ○ Stenus planifrons robustus; 8. Stenus clavicornis species group: ○ Stenus caspius, ● Stenus providus providus; 9. Stenus comma species group: ■ Stenus aereus, ○ Stenus asiaticus, ● Stenus bicornis, ▲ Stenus biguttatus, □ Stenus comma comma; 10. Stenus cordatus species group: ○ Stenus araxis, ● Stenus turk; 11. Stenus crassus and Stenus fornicatus species groups: ■ Stenus crassus, △ Stenus formicetorum, ○ Stenus fornicatus; 12. Stenus glacialis species group: ➕ Stenus armeniacus, ▲ Stenus hospes, ■ Stenus limicola, ○ Stenus medus, ▲ Stenus parcior, □ Stenus persicus, ● Stenus schah." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures7-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74429" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">12</figureCitation>
). Besides a find in the Ardabil Province, we repeatedly collected it in the Zagros Mountains from Kordestan southwards to northern Fars, usually in higher elevations and sympatrically with relatives of the 
<taxonomicName id="68B162119AAC5A5D8F9AD4DD5B8CE2E5" authorityName="Heer" authorityYear="1839" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus glacialis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis id="ADE68B373A5C891DD06131F00FDBD5CA" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Stenus glacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group such as 
<taxonomicName id="2DC8142A1EBAC09FF28385E7EA69BAC3" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1840" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus hospes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hospes">
<emphasis id="A592AC3A918A64CBAFEC4E8B6DD73A44" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Stenus hospes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B6626899F06E8F9706D6DB99FC74CC3E" authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus schah" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schah">
<emphasis id="2E5B3A035DD15966E30A38374CCA4687" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Stenus schah</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="81123E9B59E300553BDF962B384DE1FA" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" type="biogeographical characterization">
<paragraph id="B4DB653E6051EE7CCBF49CA066305266" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Biogeographical characterization.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="044AB0A4F67D7E4BDEAAE20FA3A56BD6" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
Judging from the distribution pattern in the Zagros Mountains and Northwest Iran (Ardabil Province), 
<taxonomicName id="296AC76A7BE68544C72845F4347EEC8C" authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus persicus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis id="3DE075B74D287A146EA67948A20B07DF" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Stenus persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be regarded as an Iranian faunal element.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
